OpenCV as a Console App

Very common in C++.
	Examples:
		Batch image processing
		Video analysis from files
		Image format conversion
		Face detection on stored images
		CCTV backend processing
		ML inference pipelines
---------------------------------
eg.
    ./vision_app input.jpg output.jpg

    int main(int argc, char** argv) {
        cv::Mat img = cv::imread("img.jpg");
        cv::Mat gray;
        cv::cvtColor(img, gray, cv::COLOR_BGR2GRAY);
        cv::imwrite("out.jpg", gray);
    }

No window, no mouse, no GUI.
----------------------------------------
Headless OpenCV (real-world usage)

In production systems:
	No monitor
	No keyboard
	Runs as a service

Used in:
	Traffic cameras
	Surveillance servers
	Factory inspection systems
	Robotics pipelines
	Cloud vision services

This is pure console / service mode.
